Class ParamListServiceConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • EasyOverrider.ParamListServiceConfig

  • public class ParamListServiceConfig

        Any parameter passed in as null will maintain the default value.
        Parameters:
        stringForNull - the String to use for a null value - default is "null"
        stringForRecursionPrevented - the String to use to indicate recursion was prevented - default is "..."
        stringForEmptyParamList - the String to use when there are no parameters - default is " "
        parameterDelimiter - the String to use as a delimiter between parameters - default is ", "
        nameValueFormat - the format to use to create name/value pair Strings - default is "%1$s=%2$s"
        parameterValueFormat - the format to use for each parameter - default is "'%1$s'"
        toStringFormat - the format to use for the final toString result - default is "%1$s@%2$s [%3$s]"
        classNameGetter - the Function that converts a class into a String - default is Class::getSimpleName
        hashCodeToString - the function that converts a hashCode int to a String - default is Integer::toHexString
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a provided format String is invalid.
